m_q.target_metric: RMSE between NRLMSISE-00 predicted neutral density and Swarm-B measured neutral density for all 2024 observations
sub_questions: Extract F10.7, F10.7A, daily Ap, and 3-hour Ap vector from OMNI2 data
Prepare NRLMSISE-00 model inputs from OMNI2 data
Run NRLMSISE-00 model for each Swarm-B observation timestamp
Extract measured neutral density from Swarm-B POD files
Calculate RMSE between predicted and measured densities

schema_conflicts: Swarm-B files have date and time in separate columns (col0 and col1), OMNI2 has combined datetime
Swarm-B column names are generic (col0-col8), OMNI2 column names are numeric codes
OMNI2 data format requires reference to omni2.text for column interpretation

scale_issues: Neutral density values in scientific notation (e.g., 0.30634757E-12)
OMNI2 data contains placeholder values (999999.99, 99999.99) that need filtering
Swarm-B time resolution is 30 seconds, OMNI2 is hourly
cross_source_conflicts: Time alignment: Swarm-B 30-second data vs OMNI2 hourly data requires temporal interpolation
Geographic coordinates vs solar/magnetic coordinates for NRLMSISE-00 inputs

format_notes: Swarm-B files: No header, 9 columns, date and time separate
OMNI2 data files: No header, 55 columns, numeric column names
OMNI2 text file: Contains format specification with column descriptions
Neutral density values use 'E' notation for scientific format

constraints: Must use only OMNI2 data for space weather inputs (no external feeds)
3-hour Ap vector must be constructed according to NRLMSISE-00 specification
F10.7A (81-day average) must be calculated from OMNI2 F10.7 data
Daily Ap must be derived from OMNI2 data
derived_filters: Filter out OMNI2 placeholder values (999999.99, etc.)
Ensure time alignment between Swarm-B observations and OMNI2 data
Validate geographic coordinate ranges (-90 to 90° latitude, -180 to 180° longitude)
statistical_tests: Check for missing values in time series
Validate neutral density value ranges (positive, physically plausible)
Test temporal consistency of OMNI2 indices
output_format_requirements: RMSE reported as single numeric value
Comparison should include all valid 2024 observations
NRLMSISE-00 must be run with correct input parameter ordering
